The paper discusses a system for real-time search capabilities for graph databases, which falls under the category of data management and information retrieval. Therefore, cs.DB is the most likely sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of multi-relational graphs, which suggests that it may fall under the sub-categories of cs.SI (social and information networks) and cs.DS (data structures and algorithms). The paper also discusses mining and searching for subgraph patterns, which falls under the sub-category of cs.IR (information retrieval). Finally, the paper mentions the need for an efficient approach to incremental graph search, which falls under the sub-category of cs.SD (software development and programming).
